50|$|On March 25, 2015, New York judge Thomas Griesa ordered <b>Euroclear</b> to stop {{processing}} {{payments of}} Argentina's debt bonds. This court injunction follows Argentina's decade-long dispute with its creditors. The next day, the trading bridge between <b>Euroclear</b> and Clearstream on those Argentine bonds were also shuttered until further notice. The intent of this injunction was to force Argentina to fully pay their creditors {{in order to}} gain back access to its bond-selling program.|$|E
